HEADWORD: Ruthenious
<hw>Ru*the"ni*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or containing, ruthenium; specifically, designating
those compounds in which it has a lower valence as contrasted with
<contr>ruthenic</contr> compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruthenium</ent>⟦br⟧
